# Vendored deps for on-prem / air-gapped pptx generation. Yes, we DO commit
# node_modules — that's the whole point of "vendor mode". The skill is meant
# to be a single self-contained artifact: copy the directory, run, no npm.
#
# To refresh:
#   rm -rf node_modules package-lock.json && npm install
#   git add -A && git commit
#
# Things we still don't want under git:
*.log
.DS_Store

# The native sharp prebuilt has platform-specific binaries; keep them all
# (linux-x64 + linux-arm64 cover both x86 servers and Apple-Silicon dev
# machines). Don't add platform exclusions here — that defeats the air-gap
# goal.
